              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "40-ZR-88",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.999
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 88Zr target material was",
                "produced via the 89Y(p,2n)88Zr reaction using a",
                "proton beam from the University of Alabama Cyclotron",
                "Facility at Birmingham.88Zr was chemically purified",
                "using anion-exchange chromatography and assayed before",
                "encapsulation as a salt residue in high-purity quartz",
                "tubes. The 37-kBq 88Zr samples and accompanying quartz",
                "encapsulated natural-metal foils (Fe, Zr, Mo and Y),",
                "which served as flux monitors,",
                "Each target contained 40.7 - 44.4 kBq of 88Zr at the",
                "beginning of irradiation"
              ]
            }
